[normal]Q137 [bold]&#xa0; 
[normal]Chair:[bold] Welcome to this meeting of the Scottish Affairs Committee. As you are aware, we are conducting an inquiry into land reform in 
[normal]Scotland
[normal]. We 
[normal]anticipated having two separate panels
[normal],
[normal] but because of travel difficulties we have me
[normal]rged them together. We will take
[normal] questions
[normal] to 
[normal]Andrew Leaver of Aigas Community Forest first
[normal],
[normal] and then swing on to the more general issues
[normal] and the other questions as and when
[normal]. 
[normal]              
[normal]Would the members of the panel introduce themselves for the record and indicate to us who they work for?
[normal]Andrew Leaver[bold]: I am Andrew Leaver. I am the Secretary of Aigas Community Forest, which is a community group based about 16 miles from 
[normal]Inverness
[normal]. We are attempting to purchase or take control of Forestry Commission land surrounding our village and community.
[normal]Rachael McCormack[bold]: I am Rachael Mc
[normal]Cormack, Director of Highlands and
[normal] Islands Enterprise.
[normal]Sandra Dunbar[bold]: I am Sandra Dunbar, Head of Business Improvement and Internal Audit 
[normal]at Highlands and
[normal] Islands Enterprise.
[normal]Eric Samuel[bold]: I am Eric Samuel, Senior Policy and Learning Manager at the Big Lottery Fund in 
[normal]Scotland
[normal].
[normal]Neil Ritch[bold]: I am Neil Ritch, the Deputy Director of the Big Lottery Fund in 
[normal]Scotland
[normal].
